  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "L2 learners may benefit from consciously producing clausal comparatives or other constructions that are absent or different in their L1.",
    "Our findings would improve learners' awareness of crosslinguistic contrasts.",
    "Our approach adds to the applications of accurate assessment methods, which are crucial for diagnosing learner difficulties, providing targeted feedback, and guiding instructional strategies.",
    "Following and expanding Cong (2024), we used one of the many published LLMs-related APIs called minicons (Misra 2022), which enables consistent and streamlined approach to compute surprisals from multiple LLMs.",
    "Our degree expression extraction is also built on top of one of the many existing parsers such as Stanza Manning et al. (2014)."
  ],
